# Kairox — Cursor Rules

## Project
Kairox is a local-first AI agent workbench: Rust workspace core + Tauri/Vue GUI + ratatui TUI, with native skills and plugins.

## Quick commands
- Format check: `just fmt-check` or `bun run format:check`
- Lint: `just lint` or `bun run lint`
- Test: `just test` or `cargo test --workspace --all-targets`
- Full CI gate: `just check`
- Type sync check: `just check-types`
- Desktop E2E: `just test-pilot` (starts Tauri dev app with `--features pilot`)
- Live model smoke: `just test-live`
- Run TUI: `just tui`
- Run GUI dev: `just gui-dev`
- Bump version: `just bump-version X.Y.Z`

## Language & tooling
- Rust workspace (edition 2021, resolver 2) + Vue 3 + TypeScript
- Package manager: **Bun only** (never npm, pnpm, or yarn)
- Lint: `cargo clippy -D warnings`, oxlint, Stylelint
- Format: `cargo fmt`, oxfmt

## Crate structure & dependency direction
- agent-core ← agent-runtime ← agent-tui / agent-gui / agent-eval
- agent-core ← agent-store, agent-memory, agent-models, agent-tools, agent-config, agent-mcp, agent-skills
- agent-tools → agent-mcp (re-exports `McpServerDef`, `McpTransportDef`; provides `McpToolAdapter`)
- agent-tools owns the `PolicyEngine` (orthogonal `ApprovalPolicy` × `SandboxPolicy`); legacy `PermissionMode` is removed
- agent-store owns append-only events, metadata, and trajectory persistence (`TrajectoryStore` / `SqliteTrajectoryStore`)
- agent-runtime owns session execution via `SessionActor` (`execution_runtime/`) with race-free turn-end compaction
- agent-skills provides the native skills system for reusable prompt/tool/workflow capabilities
- agent-plugins parses plugin manifests and inventories for plugin-provided skills, tools, hooks, and MCP servers
- agent-config supports layered config discovery (defaults → user → project → local), knowledge bases, hooks, and LSP/DAP server config
- agent-memory owns durable memory, context assembly, workspace RAG, and knowledge-base retriever boundaries
- agent-eval is a headless evaluation harness (binary `kairox-eval`) for JSONL scenarios with list/tag filtering, fail-fast runs, summaries, combined reports, and scenario expectations
- agent-lsp provides LSP/DAP client, transports, and server lifecycle for code intelligence and debugging
- agent-sdk provides an embeddable runtime API (`KairoxSdk`, `SdkBuilder`, `SdkSession`) for external harnesses, CI/CD, and custom UIs
- agent-runtime → agent-memory, agent-store, agent-models, agent-tools, agent-config, agent-mcp, agent-lsp
- Never create reverse dependencies. New domain types/events go in agent-core first.

Built-in `agent-tools` IDs are `shell.exec`, `fs.read`, `fs.write`, `fs.list`, `patch.apply`, `search.ripgrep`, `monitor.start`, `monitor.list`, `monitor.stop`, `browser.action`, `browser.batch`, and `computer.use`.

## Key patterns
- Workspace version: all crates use `version.workspace = true` — never set version in individual crate Cargo.toml
- Error handling: each crate has `XxxError` enum via `thiserror::Error` and `type Result<T>`
- Trait boundaries: `AppFacade`, `ModelClient`, `MemoryStore`, `EventStore`, `Tool`, `Transport`, `AgentStrategy` — use `Arc<dyn Trait>` or generics
- Context management: model metadata drives context windows; runtime budget assembly, compaction, model switching, and reasoning effort selection must remain consistent across Rust and GUI state
- Async: Tokio + `async_trait`
- Testing: Rust crate-local tests live in sibling `src/*_tests.rs` files; crate integration tests live in `crates/<crate>/tests/`, with large suites using `tests/<suite>/main.rs` plus `support` and `tests/fixtures/`
- Runtime tests use `FakeModelClient` or `ToolCallingModel`; persistence tests use in-memory SQLite stores; `live-model-tests` stays feature-gated and self-skips without credentials
- Web tests: colocate Vitest `*.test.ts` beside components/stores/composables/router code; use raw `mount()` for leaf components and `mountWithPlugins()` only when pinia/i18n/router are needed
- Playwright E2E lives in `apps/agent-gui/e2e/*.spec.ts` with `installTauriMock(page)` and domain mock fragments under `e2e/fixtures/tauri-mock/`; real desktop tauri-pilot scenarios live in `apps/agent-gui/e2e-pilot/*.toml`
- Tauri IPC: `#[tauri::command]` in `commands.rs` → Vue `invoke()` → events via `event_forwarder.rs` + `useTauriEvents.ts` (filters by session)
- When adding Rust `EventPayload` variants or command/domain types, run `just gen-types`; do not manually edit generated bindings
- Runtime structured confirmations use reserved tool id `task_confirmation.request`; GUI resolution goes through `resolve_task_confirmation`, and other consumers use `SessionFacade::decide_task_confirmation`

## Vue conventions
- Vue 3 Composition API (`<script setup lang="ts">`)
- Pinia stores: `apps/agent-gui/src/stores/`
- Composables: `apps/agent-gui/src/composables/`
- Types: `apps/agent-gui/src/types/`

## Commit format
Conventional Commits with scopes: core, runtime, models, tools, memory, store, config, mcp, lsp, skills, plugins, eval, tui, gui, docs, deps, ci

## Version bump files (must stay in sync)
1. Cargo.toml (workspace.package.version)
2. Cargo.lock (run `cargo generate-lockfile`)
3. apps/agent-gui/package.json
4. apps/agent-gui/src-tauri/tauri.conf.json
5. package.json (root)

## Common mistakes to avoid
- Using `npm`, `pnpm`, or `yarn` instead of Bun
- Setting `version` in individual crate Cargo.toml
- Hardcoding API keys (use agent-config's `api_key_env`)
- Forgetting to run `just gen-types` when changing Rust events, commands, or generated TypeScript bindings
- Forgetting to register new Tauri commands in both `generate_handler!` (invocation) and `collect_commands!` (specta type-gen)
- Skipping `bun install` after creating a git worktree
- Editing `apps/agent-gui/src/generated/{commands,events}.ts` by hand — these are auto-generated, run `just gen-types`
- Forgetting to update `apps/agent-gui/e2e/tauri-mock.js` when adding new `#[tauri::command]` or events
